  <discussion>Species 2 (1 in flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>Globulinella can be recognized by its small stature, spathulate or oval leaves with broadly rounded, cucullate apex, and strong, laterally spurred costa ending below the apex.  The plants grow in crevices or protected places on the sides of calcareous boulders or ledges.  Gemmae have been reported by R. H. Zander (1993) from a Mexican collection.</discussion>
